review_blob:
500ml Bottle, 2 or so years old, no date on the bottle.

Pours a deep, opaque black, deep brown head that stays put for a spell. Nose diving reveals rich and robust chocolate, almost like smelling dark chocolate syrup, hints of soy sauce, lots of roasted malt smells. First sip reveals wonderful flavors of roasted malt balanced with flavors of dark fruit and little to no hop flavor. Sipping more I get cherries, vanilla, and some delightful sweetness. I do love this stout and hop to pick up a younger one. Well balanced with no lingering flavor, making you want to keep going back.
Pours with a thin head, nothing special.  Smells a little sour, like a vegitable-ish smell.  Taste doesnt wow me either.  A basic pale ale. When this one ends, it wont be so bitter.
beer_name: Two Brothers The Bitter End Pale Ale

review_blob: Smells great, but thats about it.  I fail to see the cappuccino part of this stout.  Its a coffee stout yes, but I dont see the like a vanilla, or even a milkish flavor, maybe they shouldve used lactose.  Who knows.  I like this, but I dont think I would run to buy a case when it was released.
Pours with a yellowish head, dark amber in color, good carbonation.  Smells of hops with citrus tones.  Good malt flavor followed by a hoppy finish.  Medium thick mouth feel.

Pours with a thick white head that fades in a few minutes to a smaller head.  Surprisingly clear for such a big beer.  Tons of hop noteswith a little citrus.  Good stong hoppy flavor, and a thick mouth feel.  Does its job, but then I like big beers.
Pours with a nice thickish head that fades  to a whisp within a few minutes.  Nutty smells and flavors.  Not much on mouth feel.  decent beer, and my first dunkleweizen.

Pours with a very thick head, smells of pine and hops, some citrus.  Good inital taste that gives way to a thick  finish.  Great bitter taste and the balance of the 7 hops is very good.  Good big IPA.

Finally mustered up the gul to buy one, good lord what a hoppy beer, shoulda saved this for a night I wanted something a little bigger, I want to just get in the bed.  BUt the beer, it is amazing, hoppier than a bunny and clody yellow, amazing beer!
This beer didnt do much for me, it had a nice fruity head, Pretty, transparent yellow.  Not my fav, but its ok.
Amanzing odor, very unique smell, very pretty reddish color. Sweet flavor, strong alcohol flavor, perhaps too much so.  Heavy and fuzzy/bubbly mouth feel.
beer_name: Flying Dog Horn Dog Barley Wine

review_blob: Sweet smell, chocolate, sugar, deep black, black color, very heavy mouth feel,smooth finish.
Flowery, earth odor, thyme,, pours a cloudy brown with a nice tan head that whisps to a thin head in a few minutes.  Starts off creamy smooth, sweet flavour then a sourness.
Pours a deep amber/red, weak head, fizzes out in about a minute.  Stong hoppy smell,, hard bite, decent red ale.
beer_name: Rogue Dry Hopped St. Rogue Red Ale

review_blob: Not a fan of the aroma, average appearence, nothing special, weak taste, I honestly expected more here.
Bitter honey flavor, bubbles stay even few mintues after the beer is poured.  Pretty golden honey color.
Aroma fades in over time.  Nice red color, head stays on after a few minutes.  Nice peppery finish, this is a fun beer, but I would not have this all the time.
Amazing, complicated smell, great red color, redish brown with a nutty colored head. Great bitterish flavor.  Of the scotch ales i have tried lately, this one is the top for me. Amazing.

POurs a nice dark color from the glass with a nice tan head that fades to a thin whispy head in a few minutes. Bland smell, the slightest hint of chocolate after tasting.  I didnt find this to be as impressive as some of the other beers I have been drinking as of late.  Good taste overall, I would pick this over some other beers.

I get the smeel of raisins, and a deep roasty smell.  THe beer poured with a nice thick dark tan head. Great roasted hop flavor, lots of chocolate, coffe hints, but the raisin taste still pokes through, thick as hell.
Complex woodey, chocolate and other aromas, nice dark brown/red almost purple.  Thin head that faded.  Nice chocolate malted flavors.  Very unique beer, I really like this.
beer_name: Three Floyds Robert The Bruce Scottish Ale

review_blob: Smokey aroma, coffee, chocolate, Completely black and very thick out of the bottle.  Lasting medium sized tan head.  Wow, nice bite to it, I like the dark bitter taste. Light pallet, quite smooth, dry at the end, i will pick this up again.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Black, opaque color, chocolate nose, bitter flavor.thick palate.  I expected more of a chocolate/coffee punch from this.  I like it though.  I was in the mood for a good porter, and I got one.
UPDATED: FEB 7, 2007

Wow, hoppy as hell smell; the odor attacked me when I opened the bottle.  Deep pretty red color.  Thin,weak head that barely lasted, thin mouth feel.  Heavy Hop taste.  I will be buying another bottle to share with friends.
Creamy white head.  Apricot smell. Apricot taste, would be fun to cook with.  Not a favorite, but its pretty good.
Chocolate nose, slight coffee, thick, opaque black, whiteish head, strong coffee notes, thick pallet, heavy mouth feel.  Amazing beer, I like this more than the Stone Russian Imperial.
Sweet, flowery nose, not very impressive looks wise, like an orange soda.  Thick palate, pleasent feel in mouth.  Nice mild flavor, sweet with fruit notes.
Good dark color, flat pallet.  Nice tannish head.  Deep, bitey smokey flavor.  I like this more than I liked their pale ale.
To be honest, I wasnt the biggest fan of this beer.  I found it to be a bit to bitter.  I did however have a delightful, smooth pallet.  Maybe its because I am a tad stuffy.
Fruity and spicy fruity.  Smokey amber color.  Great beer.  White head, one of the better beers I have had, but I still prefer Delerium Belgian Ale.
Bitter,  sorta tangy...little tacky after taste.  Wouldnt be my first choice...but wouldnt complain if it was given to me.
It has a tangy taste.  Brilliant red color, bad atmittedly I picked it because of the color.  Nutty complicated flavor.  Fruity and nutty all at once.  Thick palat feel in my opinion.
UPDATED: FEB 12, 2007
